---
import { FieldDemo } from '../../components/FieldDemo';
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
import { meta } from './_meta/field';
---

<DocsLayout title={meta.label} description={meta.description}>
  <section class="gw-section">
    <div class="gw-width gw-stack--lg">
      <div class="gw-prose">
        <h1 class="gw-heading-l">Field</h1>
        <p>Field is the primary form API. It renders the label, hint, error copy, and ARIA description wiring for the control.</p>
        <h2 class="gw-heading-m">When to use</h2>
        <p>Use Field for every text input, textarea, and select. Width hints communicate the expected answer length.</p>
        <h2 class="gw-heading-m">When not to use</h2>
        <p>Do not render an orphaned input and add label markup manually unless you are building a lower-level primitive.</p>
      </div>

      <section class="gw-card gw-stack">
        <h2 class="gw-heading-m">Demo</h2>
        <FieldDemo />
      </section>

      <section class="gw-card gw-stack">
        <h2 class="gw-heading-m">Accessibility notes</h2>
        <p class="gw-body--sm">Field provides the structural relationship between label, hint, error copy, and the control. It supplies <code class="gw-mono">aria-labelledby</code>, <code class="gw-mono">aria-describedby</code>, and <code class="gw-mono">aria-invalid</code> props to the child render function.</p>
        <p class="gw-body--sm">Consumers must pass those props to exactly one form control and keep the visible label specific to the answer being requested.</p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </section>
</DocsLayout>
